me watch reruns

00:01:27.756 --> 00:01:31.486 A:middle
of the 1960s Spider-Man
cartoon that was kind of made

00:01:31.486 --> 00:01:33.266 A:middle
up with panels from
the comic book.

00:01:34.006 --> 00:01:38.016 A:middle
And something about Spider-Man
just grabbed my attention.

00:01:38.426 --> 00:01:41.666 A:middle
I don't know if it was
those bright primary colors;

00:01:41.666 --> 00:01:43.146 A:middle
the red and the blue.

00:01:43.146 --> 00:01:45.186 A:middle
Perhaps it was his
big white eyes.

00:01:45.456 --> 00:01:47.386 A:middle
Maybe it was because
he was young and funny.

00:01:47.386 --> 00:01:48.916 A:middle
I don't know, but something

00:01:48.916 --> 00:01:50.376 A:middle
about Spider-Man
really grabbed me

00:01:50.376 --> 00:01:52.946 A:middle
like no other character
had before.

00:01:53.666 --> 00:01:56.406 A:middle
In fact, I was into him so much
I remember two years later,

00:01:56.406 --> 00:02:00.966 A:middle
it was the book fair for my
second grade class at school,

00:01:56.406 --> 00:02:00.966 A:middle
it was the book fair for my
second grade class at school,

00:02:01.586 --> 00:02:03.746 A:middle
and I walked in and there

00:02:03.746 --> 00:02:06.866 A:middle
against the back wall
I saw Spider-Man.

00:02:07.366 --> 00:02:09.716 A:middle
Not actually Spider-Man,
it was a small reprint,

00:02:10.386 --> 00:02:13.176 A:middle
a paperback sized reprint
