sophomore year at college.

00:02:54.176 --> 00:02:56.216 A:middle
It was -- I remember
it was one evening

00:02:56.456 --> 00:02:58.856 A:middle
and I saw some weird
lights out the window.

00:02:58.856 --> 00:03:01.926 A:middle
This was an apartment I was
living in with my mother,

00:02:58.856 --> 00:03:01.926 A:middle
This was an apartment I was
living in with my mother,

00:03:01.926 --> 00:03:04.816 A:middle
my parents had divorced
when I was in high school.

00:03:05.566 --> 00:03:06.466 A:middle
So, I saw these weird lights.

00:03:06.466 --> 00:03:09.016 A:middle
I go outside and I see
that the apartment building

00:03:09.016 --> 00:03:10.986 A:middle
that we live in is on fire.

00:03:11.996 --> 00:03:14.826 A:middle
And the flames were
starting over on one side

00:03:14.826 --> 00:03:17.346 A:middle
and our apartment
unit was down here.

00:03:18.066 --> 00:03:19.846 A:middle
And as the flames started going

00:03:19.846 --> 00:03:22.796 A:middle
across the building I
was running in and out

00:03:22.956 --> 00:03:24.716 A:middle
of the apartment
building grabbing things

00:03:24.776 --> 00:03:26.786 A:middle
that I thought we
couldn't replace.

00:03:27.366 --> 00:03:32.016 A:middle
So, these were years before we
had such things as an iPhone,

00:03:32.016 --> 00:03:36.006 A:middle
I know horrible, so our
pictures were physical,

00:03:36.006 --> 00:03:37.236 A:middle
they were in photo albums.

00:03:37.236 --> 00:03:39.316 A:middle
So, I was running in
and out of the building,

00:03:39.516 --> 00:03:42.396 A:middle
our apartment building,
grabbing photo albums,

00:03:42.396 --> 00:03:45.026 A:middle
I was grabbing some
pieces of furniture,

00:03:45.026 --> 00:03:48.226 A:middle
pictures off the wall,
whatever I could grab

00:03:48.226 --> 00:03:50.616 A:middle
that I thought had
sentimental value.

00:03:51.046 --> 00:03:53.316 A:middle
And then I remember
the lights went

00:03:53.316 --> 00:03:55.516 A:middle
out in the building,
no more electricity.

00:03:56.156 --> 00:03:57.976 A:middle
And I knew I had one
more chance to go in.

00:03:59.126 --> 00:04:03.036 A:middle
So, I run in, I can't see
really, I'm feeling my way

00:03:59.126 --> 00:04:03.036 A:middle
So, I run in, I can't see
really, I'm feeling my way

00:04:03.036 --> 00:04:06.606 A:middle
through the apartment, down
the hallway, into my bedroom,

00:04:07.036 --> 00:04:09.916 A:middle
I open my closet door
to get one more thing

00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:14.036 A:middle
from the apartment,
a box of comic books.

00:04:15.056 --> 00:04:16.906 A:middle
Now you might think
that's kind of crazy.

00:04:16.906 --> 00:04:18.935 A:middle
Why would someone run
into a building that's

00:04:18.935 --> 00:04:21.526 A:middle
on fire to get comic books?

00:04:23.176 --> 00:04:25.576 A:middle
Well, I mean at that moment
it kind of crystalized

00:04:25.576 --> 00:04:28.886 A:middle
in my mind how much the comics

00:04:29.316 --> 00:04:31.836 A:middle
and these characters
meant to me.

00:04:33.056 --> 00:04:35.926 A:middle
So, I mentioned my parents
had a divorce, and if anyone

00:04:35.926 --> 00:04:39.106 A:middle
who has been through a divorce,
or experienced it as a child,

00:04:39.156 --> 00:04:41.756 A:middle
you know how unsettling it is,

00:04:42.016 --> 00:04:45.486 A:middle
and it sort of rolls this
grenade into your life.

00:04:45.486 --> 00:04:49.366 A:middle
But during that, during
our moving around,

00:04:49.786 --> 00:04:52.776 A:middle
whatever was happening in
my life, and even the fire,

00:04:52.776 --> 00:04:56.216 A:middle
I had really good friends,
friends that helped me

00:04:56.386 --> 00:04:58.476 A:middle
through these events in my life.

00:04:59.136 --> 00:05:01.946 A:middle
And luckily those friends helped
guide me eventually to work

00:04:59.136 --> 00:05:01.946 A:middle
And luckily those friends helped
guide me eventually to work

00:05:01.946 --> 00:05:06.746 A:middle
for Marvel, the company I dreamt
of working for ever since I was

00:05:06.746 --> 00:05:09.046 A:middle
that little kid watching
the cartoon.

00:05:09.686 --> 00:05:13.066 A:middle
And when I got to Marvel, that's
when the real learning began,

00:05:13.906 --> 00:05:15.376 A:middle
and that's when that mantra,

00:05:15.786 --> 00:05:19.746 A:middle
with great power comes great
responsibility, really sunk in.

00:05:20.606 --> 00:05:23.566 A:middle
See not only does it
apply to our characters,

00:05:23.746 --> 00:05:26.686 A:middle
and the decisions they must
make with their abilities,

00:05:27.086 --> 00:05:30.436 A:middle
it also applies to us,
the employees at Marvel.

00:05:31.476 --> 00:05:35.036 A:middle
So, we say to ourselves,
what is our power.

00:05:35.886 --> 00:05:38.256 A:middle
Well, our power is
we're able to work

00:05:38.256 --> 00:05:40.866 A:middle
with these amazing
characters, only we can.

00:05:42.136 --> 00:05:45.626 A:middle
Our other power is our
storytelling skills.

00:05:46.246 --> 00:05:49.026 A:middle
We think we're pretty good at
telling stories, whether it's

00:05:49.026 --> 00:05:52.326 A:middle
in film, or in print,
or through video games.

00:05:52.796 --> 00:05:54.696 A:middle
That's where I work now,
as the Creative Director

00:05:54.696 --> 00:05:56.576 A:middle
for the Marvel Games Division.

00:05:57.496 --> 00:06:00.726 A:middle
So, if that is our power, the
characters and the stories

00:05:57.496 --> 00:06:00.726 A:middle
So, if that is our power, the
characters and the stories

00:06:00.726 --> 00:06:03.656 A:middle
that we tell with them,
what is our responsibility?

00:06:04.746 --> 00:06:07.526 A:middle
Well, our responsibilities
are to create stories

00:06:07.526 --> 00:06:10.026 A:middle
that in some way help people.

00:06:10.926 --> 00:06:14.226 A:middle
That connect to them,
that speak to them,

00:06:14.656 --> 00:06:19.336 A:middle
and hopefully give them
inspiration in a way

00:06:19.336 --> 00:06:22.036 A:middle
that they can then
apply it to their lives.

00:06:22.516 --> 00:06:27.316 A:middle
Now, I mentioned I had
some friends, some friends

00:06:27.316 --> 00:06:30.686 A:middle
that helped me through my
life and led me to Marvel,

00:06:31.336 --> 00:06:33.306 A:middle
and to embrace power
and responsibility.

00:06:33.896 --> 00:06:37.606 A:middle
And even though we grew
up at different times,

00:06:38.256 --> 00:06:40.486 A:middle
probably in different
locations around America,

00:06:40.486 --> 00:06:44.606 A:middle
and if not around the world,
I think you know my friends.

00:06:45.616 --> 00:06:47.096 A:middle
I think you do.

