So, here is the cover
to his first comic.

00:08:11.556 --> 00:08:13.276 A:middle
See the date up there, 1941.

00:08:13.846 --> 00:08:17.376 A:middle
And what's remarkable and
really cool about this cover?

00:08:17.806 --> 00:08:19.116 A:middle
Well, what is he doing on it?

00:08:19.426 --> 00:08:20.196 A:middle
Who's he punching?

00:08:21.216 --> 00:08:23.696 A:middle
Hitler! Because that's
what you would do, right?

00:08:23.696 --> 00:08:25.576 A:middle
If you were in a room with
Hitler and you had the shield

00:08:25.576 --> 00:08:27.636 A:middle
and the powers, you'd sock
him in the jaw [laughter].

00:08:29.616 --> 00:08:32.155 A:middle
Little problem with that.

00:08:32.196 --> 00:08:36.226 A:middle
See, this comic was
published in the summer, 1941.

00:08:36.976 --> 00:08:41.586 A:middle
Months before December,
months before Pearl Harbor,

00:08:42.346 --> 00:08:46.336 A:middle
months before America was
officially entered into the war.

00:08:47.626 --> 00:08:52.206 A:middle
So, when his creators, Jack
Kirby and Joe Simon came

00:08:52.206 --> 00:08:55.916 A:middle
to work they were in trouble.

00:08:56.896 --> 00:09:00.736 A:middle
There were protesters
outside and when they got

00:08:56.896 --> 00:09:00.736 A:middle
There were protesters
outside and when they got

00:09:00.736 --> 00:09:03.156 A:middle
up into the offices
of Timely Comics,

00:09:03.156 --> 00:09:05.516 A:middle
and that's what Marvel was
before they were Marvel,

00:09:05.516 --> 00:09:08.846 A:middle
they were called Timely,
they got up to the offices,

00:09:08.846 --> 00:09:11.776 A:middle
they were yelled at
by the publisher.

00:09:12.676 --> 00:09:15.986 A:middle
He said, Jack and Joe,
what are you doing?

00:09:16.616 --> 00:09:18.386 A:middle
You've published a comic book

00:09:18.726 --> 00:09:22.176 A:middle
with a character named
Captain America, of all things,

00:09:22.486 --> 00:09:25.616 A:middle
and he's wrapped in the
American Flag, and he's punching

00:09:25.616 --> 00:09:27.816 A:middle
in the face the leader
of a country

00:09:28.056 --> 00:09:29.526 A:middle
that we are not at war with.

00:09:30.646 --> 00:09:31.896 A:middle
What the hell are you doing?

00:09:31.976 --> 00:09:34.616 A:middle
Now, it was at that
moment someone came running

00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:36.976 A:middle
in from the sales department;
boss, boss, look at the numbers!

00:09:41.046 --> 00:09:41.666 A:middle
Keep doing it [laughter].

00:09:41.666 --> 00:09:46.376 A:middle
It was an immediate
hit, sold out.

00:09:47.196 --> 00:09:48.956 A:middle
Why? Because it was
wish fulfillment.

00:09:49.856 --> 00:09:53.006 A:middle
Jack and Joe were
using comic books

00:09:53.006 --> 00:09:56.226 A:middle
as their art form
to make a statement.

00:09:57.046 --> 00:09:58.386 A:middle
They were both Jewish.

00:09:59.026 --> 00:10:01.866 A:middle
They had relatives and
friends back in Europe.

00:09:59.026 --> 00:10:01.866 A:middle
They had relatives and
friends back in Europe.

00:10:02.336 --> 00:10:03.966 A:middle
They knew what was going on.

00:10:04.976 --> 00:10:06.716 A:middle
They knew about the ghettos.

00:10:06.796 --> 00:10:08.806 A:middle
They knew about the work camps.

00:10:09.126 --> 00:10:11.716 A:middle
They knew what the
Nazis were doing

00:10:12.566 --> 00:10:18.996 A:middle
and they thought America should
go over there and stop them.

00:10:19.206 --> 00:10:21.106 A:middle
It's also important -- what
did they give Captain America?

00:10:21.106 --> 00:10:22.106 A:middle
What is he holding?

00:10:22.526 --> 00:10:23.616 A:middle
Is it a bazooka?

00:10:24.056 --> 00:10:25.376 A:middle
Is it a machine gun?

00:10:26.226 --> 00:10:27.056 A:middle
No, it's a shield.

00:10:27.646 --> 00:10:30.976 A:middle
Like I said, these
comics are an art form.

00:10:32.136 --> 00:10:33.196 A:middle
They send messages.

00:10:33.296 --> 00:10:36.576 A:middle
So, I think they chose a shield
because what does a shield do?

00:10:36.576 --> 00:10:37.986 A:middle
Well, it defends him.

00:10:37.986 --> 00:10:39.796 A:middle
Look, it's blocking that bullet.

00:10:40.916 --> 00:10:43.736 A:middle
They're saying a message
that Captain America

00:10:43.736 --> 00:10:47.006 A:middle
and America itself should
go over and protect those

00:10:47.006 --> 00:10:49.486 A:middle
that can't protect themselves.

00:10:49.876 --> 00:10:50.846 A:middle
So, it was a big hit.

00:10:50.936 --> 00:10:52.306 A:middle
But like I said, it
was controversial

00:10:52.346 --> 00:10:55.446 A:middle
because some felt we should
still be isolationists.

00:10:55.736 --> 00:10:57.986 A:middle
And why are we -- why is
he punching the leader

00:10:57.986 --> 00:10:59.256 A:middle
of this nation?

00:10:59.876 --> 00:11:02.326 A:middle
But they thought it was more
important to make the statement.

