Why can't Rogue and
Gambit just be together?

00:21:25.376 --> 00:21:26.926 A:middle
Why are you so cruel to them?

00:21:27.966 --> 00:21:29.656 A:middle
Because drama, that's why.

00:21:32.126 --> 00:21:32.636 A:middle
So, that --

00:21:33.516 --> 00:21:36.716 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:21:37.216 --> 00:21:40.166 A:middle
So, I remember I came
in and our offices

00:21:40.166 --> 00:21:42.766 A:middle
and that email account
were flooded with letters.

00:21:43.336 --> 00:21:45.316 A:middle
And some of them weren't happy.

00:21:46.316 --> 00:21:49.356 A:middle
One was from a dad, I'll never
forget it, he wrote and he said,

00:21:49.356 --> 00:21:54.846 A:middle
when my kids get home from
school I'm going to take them

00:21:54.846 --> 00:21:57.006 A:middle
to the backyard and
I'm going to stack

00:21:57.006 --> 00:21:59.256 A:middle
up all their Spider-Man comics
and I'm going to burn them.

00:21:59.766 --> 00:22:04.316 A:middle
He said, why did you make -- why
did you turn Spider Man black?

00:21:59.766 --> 00:22:04.316 A:middle
He said, why did you make -- why
did you turn Spider Man black?

00:22:04.946 --> 00:22:05.836 A:middle
Why did you do this?

00:22:05.836 --> 00:22:10.126 A:middle
Why with your East
Coast liberal views?

00:22:10.806 --> 00:22:13.296 A:middle
Why are you ruining our hero?

00:22:14.586 --> 00:22:17.126 A:middle
So, I wrote to him and I
said, Sir, you don't have

00:22:17.126 --> 00:22:21.396 A:middle
to buy a single additional
issue of this series,

00:22:22.516 --> 00:22:24.176 A:middle
but just so you know,

00:22:24.836 --> 00:22:27.866 A:middle
in the regular Marvel Universe
Peter Parker is alive and well.

00:22:28.406 --> 00:22:31.776 A:middle
But we're offering an
alternative with a Spider-Man

00:22:31.776 --> 00:22:32.706 A:middle
that looks a bit different.

00:22:33.406 --> 00:22:35.986 A:middle
So, I said, you don't have
to buy any new issues,

00:22:36.046 --> 00:22:40.156 A:middle
but please don't burn
your kids' comics.

00:22:41.246 --> 00:22:44.816 A:middle
It will not have the effect on
them that you think it will.

00:22:45.076 --> 00:22:47.256 A:middle
It will be far, far worse.

00:22:48.016 --> 00:22:48.726 A:middle
Now he didn't respond.

00:22:48.726 --> 00:22:49.926 A:middle
I don't know if he
burned them or not.

00:22:49.926 --> 00:22:51.366 A:middle
I'd like to hope he didn't.

00:22:52.006 --> 00:22:54.176 A:middle
Who can say?

00:22:54.956 --> 00:22:56.576 A:middle
But I can say, immediately
after reading

00:22:56.576 --> 00:22:57.596 A:middle
that I read a great letter.

00:22:58.896 --> 00:23:01.126 A:middle
A young woman wrote in
and said, thank you.

00:22:58.896 --> 00:23:01.126 A:middle
A young woman wrote in
and said, thank you.

00:23:01.716 --> 00:23:07.136 A:middle
She says, now my little brother
has a Spider-Man that looks just

00:23:07.136 --> 00:23:10.716 A:middle
like him, and he feels great.

00:23:11.856 --> 00:23:16.366 A:middle
He feels he is represented
up here, on this cover.

00:23:17.296 --> 00:23:17.946 A:middle
And that's why we do it.

00:23:18.516 --> 00:23:25.556 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:23:26.056 --> 00:23:28.226 A:middle
Alright, my next
friend -- let's see.

00:23:29.126 --> 00:23:31.116 A:middle
Oh, he really loved his dad.

00:23:31.926 --> 00:23:35.236 A:middle
His dad led this --
more than a business --

00:23:35.236 --> 00:23:36.716 A:middle
like an empire, you could say.

00:23:37.506 --> 00:23:39.686 A:middle
My friend really -- he
loved him, and he hoped

00:23:39.686 --> 00:23:41.246 A:middle
to one day take over for him.

00:23:42.366 --> 00:23:46.116 A:middle
And as fate would have
it, his dad was killed,

00:23:46.576 --> 00:23:51.206 A:middle
and my friend did have to step
in for him and run the empire.

00:23:51.206 --> 00:23:54.136 A:middle
And he found it was so much more
challenging than he ever knew,

00:23:54.606 --> 00:23:57.356 A:middle
and he realized it was
constantly under attack

00:23:57.756 --> 00:23:59.606 A:middle
by others outside of it.

00:23:59.606 --> 00:24:02.956 A:middle
And he had to find the
courage within himself to step

00:23:59.606 --> 00:24:02.956 A:middle
And he had to find the
courage within himself to step

00:24:02.956 --> 00:24:06.196 A:middle
into the boots of his father,
but to become his own person.

00:24:06.616 --> 00:24:10.156 A:middle
I'm talking about
The Black Panther,

00:24:11.016 --> 00:24:12.746 A:middle
who many of you may
have been introduced

00:24:12.746 --> 00:24:15.546 A:middle
to in the latest Captain
America Civil War movie.

00:24:16.246 --> 00:24:18.686 A:middle
So, Black Panther was
introduced in the pages

00:24:18.686 --> 00:24:21.126 A:middle
of The Fantastic Four, 1966.

00:24:21.406 --> 00:24:26.506 A:middle
And it was remarkable because
it was the first black character

00:24:26.506 --> 00:24:29.326 A:middle
introduced by one of the
major comic book publishers.

00:24:30.346 --> 00:24:34.386 A:middle
And what's also crazy cool is
that he was no one's sidekick.

00:24:34.876 --> 00:24:36.346 A:middle
He was no one's servant.

00:24:36.846 --> 00:24:40.136 A:middle
When the Fantastic Four
answered his invitation to go

00:24:40.136 --> 00:24:43.876 A:middle
to his nation of Wakanda,
this was a country we made

00:24:43.876 --> 00:24:45.676 A:middle
up that was in Africa.

00:24:46.136 --> 00:24:51.066 A:middle
They saw that he was a king,
and he was a king of a nation

00:24:51.066 --> 00:24:53.186 A:middle
that was the world's
most technologically

00:24:53.186 --> 00:24:54.706 A:middle
advanced country.

00:24:55.626 --> 00:24:58.766 A:middle
And so again, I think the
creators, this time Stan Lee

00:24:58.766 --> 00:25:00.466 A:middle
and Jack Kirby, were
making a statement.

00:24:58.766 --> 00:25:00.466 A:middle
and Jack Kirby, were
making a statement.

00:25:01.346 --> 00:25:05.206 A:middle
Were making a statement just in
the choices they were making.

00:25:05.726 --> 00:25:09.596 A:middle
And people loved Black
Panther right away.

00:25:09.596 --> 00:25:13.956 A:middle
And they were very smart in
the stories they told with him,

00:25:13.956 --> 00:25:17.356 A:middle
and I think they told some
very symbolic stories,

00:25:17.356 --> 00:25:18.716 A:middle
like this next cover.

00:25:19.286 --> 00:25:21.946 A:middle
So, here we are in
the 70s, and yeah,

00:25:21.946 --> 00:25:23.886 A:middle
Black Panther is
taking on the Klan.

00:25:25.306 --> 00:25:29.306 A:middle
He's actually ripping himself
off a cross before they set it

00:25:29.306 --> 00:25:30.226 A:middle
on fire.

00:25:30.756 --> 00:25:36.286 A:middle
What an emotional,
powerful, symbolic image.

00:25:36.616 --> 00:25:39.856 A:middle
One of the things I love about
him is that he's outnumbered.

00:25:40.456 --> 00:25:43.176 A:middle
I love that they chose, not
to just have one Klan member

00:25:43.176 --> 00:25:44.966 A:middle
at the bottom, but there's
a whole group of them.

00:25:45.596 --> 00:25:47.966 A:middle
This always -- this again
speaks to the Marvel message

00:25:47.966 --> 00:25:50.766 A:middle
of underdogs feeling
outnumbered,

00:25:50.896 --> 00:25:54.616 A:middle
feeling the world is against
you, but deciding to fight back,

00:25:54.616 --> 00:25:57.766 A:middle
deciding to do the
right thing anyway.

00:25:58.636 --> 00:26:04.236 A:middle
My next friend, she
was an orphan too.

00:25:58.636 --> 00:26:04.236 A:middle
My next friend, she
was an orphan too.

00:26:04.236 --> 00:26:06.186 A:middle
I think I should stop
there and talk about;

00:26:06.446 --> 00:26:10.626 A:middle
what's up with all the orphans?

00:26:10.726 --> 00:26:14.256 A:middle
Well, in any sort of art form
you have to make decisions to --

00:26:14.926 --> 00:26:16.936 A:middle
especially in fiction --
you want to get the audience

00:26:17.136 --> 00:26:20.086 A:middle
on the side of your character,
and if you have limited time,

00:26:20.156 --> 00:26:24.206 A:middle
say a limited page count of a
comic book or a limited time

00:26:24.246 --> 00:26:26.016 A:middle
in a movie or in a video game,

00:26:26.016 --> 00:26:27.776 A:middle
you have to make
choices right away

00:26:27.776 --> 00:26:30.636 A:middle
that helps your audience
connect with your character.

00:26:30.636 --> 00:26:33.386 A:middle
So, that's why you -- it's a
tradition in heroic fiction,

00:26:33.686 --> 00:26:38.006 A:middle
all these orphans; Luke
Skywalker, Harry Potter,

00:26:38.866 --> 00:26:43.486 A:middle
every Disney princess,
poor Bambi.

00:26:43.486 --> 00:26:48.696 A:middle
There goes mama [laughter]
Why do we do this?

00:26:49.856 --> 00:26:50.906 A:middle
Why do we do this?

00:26:50.906 --> 00:26:52.746 A:middle
Because again, we're
trying to get the audience

00:26:52.746 --> 00:26:53.866 A:middle
on the side of the hero.

00:26:53.866 --> 00:26:57.226 A:middle
And what's the one thing that
everyone can either fear,

00:26:58.306 --> 00:27:00.466 A:middle
or if it's unfortunate enough
to have gone through it,

00:26:58.306 --> 00:27:00.466 A:middle
or if it's unfortunate enough
to have gone through it,

00:27:00.466 --> 00:27:03.126 A:middle
to sympathize with,
losing the parents,

00:27:03.706 --> 00:27:05.076 A:middle
something everyone can fear.

00:27:05.476 --> 00:27:07.226 A:middle
So, it gets your audience
on the side of the hero.

00:27:07.226 --> 00:27:09.996 A:middle
It also literally forces the
character out of the nest.

00:27:10.296 --> 00:27:13.256 A:middle
Our characters must now
stand on their own two feet

00:27:13.256 --> 00:27:16.236 A:middle
and again make their choices
about power and responsibility.

00:27:16.236 --> 00:27:19.946 A:middle
So, that's why you often see
it in super heroes like this.

00:27:19.946 --> 00:27:22.846 A:middle
So, my next friend;
she was an orphan

00:27:23.106 --> 00:27:24.316 A:middle
and she felt like a freak.

00:27:25.556 --> 00:27:28.766 A:middle
She was like this friend,
she was born in Africa,

00:27:29.406 --> 00:27:32.606 A:middle
and she had silver hair.

00:27:33.026 --> 00:27:36.056 A:middle
She was black but she had
silver hair and she felt

00:27:36.146 --> 00:27:40.486 A:middle
like everyone was judging
her and condemning her

00:27:40.486 --> 00:27:42.786 A:middle
and thinking she was some
sort of witch or a monster.

00:27:43.186 --> 00:27:48.486 A:middle
And one day this really nice
teacher came up to her and said,

00:27:48.486 --> 00:27:50.196 A:middle
you're not cursed,
you're blessed.

00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:55.636 A:middle
I want you to come with me
to my school in Westchester

00:27:57.006 --> 00:28:00.446 A:middle
where everyone looks really
cool and we have these cool jets

00:27:57.006 --> 00:28:00.446 A:middle
where everyone looks really
cool and we have these cool jets

00:28:00.446 --> 00:28:03.196 A:middle
to fly around in, and together
we're going to go around

00:28:03.196 --> 00:28:05.586 A:middle
and we're going to show
the world that people

00:28:05.586 --> 00:28:07.006 A:middle
like you are not evil.

00:28:07.276 --> 00:28:08.866 A:middle
That people like you are good.

00:28:09.096 --> 00:28:12.356 A:middle
And we can all work together
to create a better world.

00:28:12.656 --> 00:28:14.506 A:middle
So, can you guess
my next friend?

00:28:15.226 --> 00:28:17.516 A:middle
Storm! Storm, a mutant.

00:28:17.516 --> 00:28:20.746 A:middle
In the Marvel universe we
kind of divide the characters

00:28:20.746 --> 00:28:21.836 A:middle
by how they get their powers.

00:28:22.246 --> 00:28:24.406 A:middle
So, if you get bitten
by a radioactive spider,

00:28:24.406 --> 00:28:27.106 A:middle
or if it's cosmic rays,
or if it's gamma rays,

00:28:27.536 --> 00:28:30.896 A:middle
the creators were really
grappling with the Cold War

00:28:30.896 --> 00:28:32.496 A:middle
at the time, and the
fear of the bomb.

00:28:32.496 --> 00:28:36.096 A:middle
That's why there's all this
radiation in our characters.

00:28:36.496 --> 00:28:39.326 A:middle
But if you're a mutant you
are just born different,

00:28:39.756 --> 00:28:41.196 A:middle
it's in your genes
from the start,

00:28:41.196 --> 00:28:43.606 A:middle
and when you hit puberty, ta da!

00:28:43.606 --> 00:28:48.036 A:middle
You're body starts changing,
and in the case of the mutants,

00:28:48.036 --> 00:28:50.886 A:middle
you grow wings, lasers
shoot out of your eyes.

00:28:50.886 --> 00:28:51.906 A:middle
And isn't that what you felt

00:28:51.906 --> 00:28:53.356 A:middle
like when you were
going through puberty?

00:28:54.146 --> 00:28:56.886 A:middle
I did. And so the
teacher I was talking

00:28:56.886 --> 00:28:58.386 A:middle
about is Professor X, right?

00:28:58.386 --> 00:29:00.556 A:middle
And so he comes up to
the mutants and he says,

00:28:58.386 --> 00:29:00.556 A:middle
And so he comes up to
the mutants and he says,

00:29:00.556 --> 00:29:03.106 A:middle
come with me and we're
going to change the world.

00:29:03.106 --> 00:29:05.696 A:middle
We're going to show the world
that mutants and humans can live

00:29:05.696 --> 00:29:07.506 A:middle
and work together
to change the world.

00:29:07.506 --> 00:29:09.236 A:middle
And it's a great message.

00:29:09.446 --> 00:29:11.266 A:middle
And another message
was sent by this cover.

00:29:12.296 --> 00:29:14.336 A:middle
I've mentioned America a
lot in this discussion.

00:29:14.696 --> 00:29:17.866 A:middle
And super humans are a
uniquely American invention.

00:29:18.236 --> 00:29:20.526 A:middle
We came up with them and I
think we do them really great,

00:29:20.526 --> 00:29:24.736 A:middle
and you could say right now
it's one of our greatest gifts

00:29:24.736 --> 00:29:27.266 A:middle
to the world is the super hero.

00:29:27.266 --> 00:29:29.616 A:middle
We export the super
hero around the world.

00:29:30.046 --> 00:29:32.976 A:middle
But this issue was different.

00:29:33.036 --> 00:29:36.596 A:middle
This issue introduced
international characters.

00:29:37.496 --> 00:29:39.966 A:middle
So, you have Storm
up there flying.

00:29:40.166 --> 00:29:43.286 A:middle
The big metal guy is
Colossus, he is Russian.

00:29:44.166 --> 00:29:46.166 A:middle
And to me, as a kid,
that was huge.

00:29:46.716 --> 00:29:51.196 A:middle
My mom was Ukrainian, and so I
remember growing up in the 80s,

00:29:51.196 --> 00:29:52.796 A:middle
you know anyone from
Eastern European,

00:29:52.796 --> 00:29:53.896 A:middle
and anywhere near Russia was,

00:29:54.116 --> 00:29:56.156 A:middle
you know those were
commies, they're evil.

00:29:56.156 --> 00:29:59.806 A:middle
But in the comics I saw that,
no, Russians can be good.

00:29:59.866 --> 00:30:01.036 A:middle
Colossus is a hero.

00:29:59.866 --> 00:30:01.036 A:middle
Colossus is a hero.

00:30:01.086 --> 00:30:02.586 A:middle
It meant a lot to me.

00:30:02.956 --> 00:30:06.136 A:middle
So, also you see Nightcrawler,
with the blue face, he's German.

00:30:06.376 --> 00:30:09.126 A:middle
Wolverine, with the
claws, from Canada.

00:30:10.906 --> 00:30:11.566 A:middle
True story.

00:30:13.286 --> 00:30:14.066 A:middle
International group.

00:30:14.406 --> 00:30:18.326 A:middle
Again, I think they were making
a choice deliberately to say,

00:30:18.436 --> 00:30:20.406 A:middle
again, it doesn't
matter who you are

00:30:20.406 --> 00:30:23.876 A:middle
or where you come from,
we can all be heroes.

00:30:23.956 --> 00:30:24.816 A:middle
We can all be heroes.

00:30:25.066 --> 00:30:26.316 A:middle
And storm was really unique

00:30:26.316 --> 00:30:29.466 A:middle
because she wasn't only
just really powerful,

00:30:29.686 --> 00:30:31.936 A:middle
she can control the weather,
she can make it thunder

00:30:31.936 --> 00:30:33.056 A:middle
and lightning and storm.

00:30:33.446 --> 00:30:37.316 A:middle
Not only that, but she had
real strength of character.

00:30:37.316 --> 00:30:38.436 A:middle
I mean look at this next cover.

00:30:38.966 --> 00:30:41.046 A:middle
That's her rocking
the Grace Jones look,

00:30:41.076 --> 00:30:43.226 A:middle
with the mohawk and the leather.

00:30:43.476 --> 00:30:45.096 A:middle
And she was saying to the
world, hey this is me.

00:30:45.446 --> 00:30:47.486 A:middle
Love me or hate me,
this is who I am.

00:30:47.486 --> 00:30:49.476 A:middle
Now, this issue was significant

00:30:49.476 --> 00:30:52.836 A:middle
because she actually challenged
Cyclops for leadership

00:30:52.836 --> 00:30:56.506 A:middle
of the X-Men, and she did it
at a time when she was zapped

00:30:57.176 --> 00:30:59.756 A:middle
by a gun and she didn't
even have her mutant powers.

00:31:00.636 --> 00:31:03.596 A:middle
But she was very smart
and she was crafty,

00:31:03.956 --> 00:31:05.806 A:middle
and she beat Cyclops.

00:31:07.086 --> 00:31:09.666 A:middle
So, here I am, this white kid.

00:31:09.666 --> 00:31:12.346 A:middle
At the time I was living
down south in Tennessee,

00:31:12.736 --> 00:31:16.866 A:middle
and I read a comic book where a
black woman defeats a white man

00:31:17.106 --> 00:31:21.466 A:middle
for leadership of Marvel's most
popular and powerful super team.

00:31:22.046 --> 00:31:25.546 A:middle
And you know what I said, and
readers around the world said?

00:31:26.036 --> 00:31:26.796 A:middle
We said, alright!

00:31:27.496 --> 00:31:29.336 A:middle
Cool! She's earned it.

00:31:29.766 --> 00:31:32.466 A:middle
So, I think stories like this,

00:31:32.466 --> 00:31:34.616 A:middle
and images like this,
they have an impact.

00:31:35.326 --> 00:31:38.736 A:middle
And Storm isn't the only
powerful female that we have.

00:31:38.736 --> 00:31:41.076 A:middle
We actually have a
tradition of strong women.

00:31:41.276 --> 00:31:44.246 A:middle
In the movies you've seen Black
Widow and Scarlett, which,

00:31:44.246 --> 00:31:45.316 A:middle
we announced we're finally going

00:31:45.316 --> 00:31:47.626 A:middle
to do a female solo
movie, Captain Marvel.

00:31:47.996 --> 00:31:51.506 A:middle
We have a history of
these strong women and we

00:31:51.506 --> 00:31:53.686 A:middle
like to celebrate them.

00:31:53.686 --> 00:31:56.346 A:middle
So, this year we did an
event called Women of Power.

00:31:56.346 --> 00:31:59.126 A:middle
We were going to -- it
was kind of a salute

00:31:59.126 --> 00:32:01.326 A:middle
to International
Women's History Day.

00:31:59.126 --> 00:32:01.326 A:middle
to International
Women's History Day.

00:32:01.326 --> 00:32:03.226 A:middle
And so we said, let's do a
whole month to celebrate.

00:32:03.576 --> 00:32:05.636 A:middle
So, up top you see these images.

00:32:06.256 --> 00:32:07.796 A:middle
We created these covers.

00:32:07.886 --> 00:32:10.576 A:middle
We created 24 different
variant covers that were going

00:32:10.576 --> 00:32:11.656 A:middle
to go on our comic books.

00:32:11.656 --> 00:32:14.506 A:middle
And I knew we were doing
this months in advance.

00:32:14.886 --> 00:32:16.596 A:middle
So, I called up my
friends in publishing,

00:32:16.596 --> 00:32:19.586 A:middle
because at this point I'm now --
was over in California working

00:32:19.586 --> 00:32:21.716 A:middle
for the Marvel Games team
as Creative Director --

00:32:21.716 --> 00:32:23.806 A:middle
and I said, hey, let's team up.

00:32:23.806 --> 00:32:26.856 A:middle
I want to do women of
power in our games.

00:32:26.856 --> 00:32:28.136 A:middle
And they said, well how
are you going to do that?

00:32:28.136 --> 00:32:31.376 A:middle
I said, I'm going to call all
of our different partners,

00:32:31.806 --> 00:32:35.126 A:middle
who create all of our mobile
games, and I'm going to ask them

00:32:35.396 --> 00:32:36.396 A:middle
if they want to participate.

00:32:36.396 --> 00:32:39.116 A:middle
I'm going to say, hey do you
have any female characters

00:32:39.426 --> 00:32:40.746 A:middle
that you were going to
introduce in the games?

00:32:40.746 --> 00:32:44.726 A:middle
Do you want to hold
them until that month?

00:32:44.916 --> 00:32:47.566 A:middle
And everyone whose logo
you see up there said, yes!

00:32:47.566 --> 00:32:50.426 A:middle
And so we did the Women
of Power event in games.

00:32:50.746 --> 00:32:52.716 A:middle
It was covered by
Entertainment Weekly,

00:32:52.716 --> 00:32:54.116 A:middle
and then Forbes picked it up.

00:32:54.986 --> 00:32:57.756 A:middle
And it was a way for
us to make a statement

00:32:57.756 --> 00:32:59.296 A:middle
without even saying anything.

00:32:59.586 --> 00:33:01.646 A:middle
See, at the time,
you know the story

00:32:59.586 --> 00:33:01.646 A:middle
See, at the time,
you know the story

00:33:01.646 --> 00:33:04.116 A:middle
of Gamer Gate was in the news.

00:33:04.116 --> 00:33:06.066 A:middle
And people were asking me, what
do you think of Gamer Gate?

00:33:06.066 --> 00:33:07.906 A:middle
And I said, what do I think?

00:33:07.966 --> 00:33:10.226 A:middle
I -- we love our female readers.

00:33:10.786 --> 00:33:12.286 A:middle
We love our female characters.

00:33:12.736 --> 00:33:16.536 A:middle
We love our -- most of
our staff is female.

00:33:16.886 --> 00:33:20.776 A:middle
We want to invite
everybody to the party.

00:33:21.876 --> 00:33:24.886 A:middle
And that's what the Women
of Power event represented.

00:33:24.886 --> 00:33:27.226 A:middle
And that's what it
said with us having

00:33:27.226 --> 00:33:28.486 A:middle
to make a statement on it.

00:33:29.256 --> 00:33:29.976 A:middle
My last-- Yes!

00:33:30.516 --> 00:33:36.096 A:middle
[ Applause ]

